originalText.text: I have accessed my fair share of government agencies, and this was by far the best experience I've had. Michael was incredible and enrolled me in health insurance. He even emailed me after with providers in my area. I came because I couldn't get a rep on the phone to finish my unemployment application. I was in and out of the building in 45 minutes with my application complete and health insurance for a year!

originalText.text: This was the most efficient government office I have ever been to. Everyone, from the security guards to the receptionist and the people who worked on my case were extremely professional, kind and warm. Thank you so much!

originalText.text: Anyone who gave this organization and office a bad review was either rude, disrespectful, unprepared, or all the above. My experience was extremely pleasant, starting from the front desk reception/security, to the security escorts, amd the security officer on the main floor. Michael was kind enough to come up and offer free health care, information and his card saying contact him should you have any questions. Miss Lynn was extremely helpful in finding me a manager, David who came out and helped me get on the line to unemployment and ACTUALLY get an agent! Something which you can never do from home. Last, but not least, Mr. Tony Wilson was a true help and trooper as he walked me through the tedious process of setting up my ID account. I cannot compliment them enough. Again, as I said earlier, if you complain about this office then you are the issue, not them. They were great.
